#: ../../extending/extending.rst:874
msgid "Reference Counts"
msgstr "ReferensrûÊkningar"

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:876
msgid ""
"In languages like C or C++, the programmer is responsible for dynamic "
"allocation and deallocation of memory on the heap.  In C, this is done using "
"the functions :c:func:`malloc` and :c:func:`free`.  In C++, the operators "
"``new`` and ``delete`` are used with essentially the same meaning and we'll "
"restrict the following discussion to the C case."
msgstr ""
"I sprûËk som C eller C++ ûÊr programmeraren ansvarig fûÑr dynamisk allokering "
"och avallokering av minne pûË heapen.  I C gûÑrs detta med hjûÊlp av "
"funktionerna :c:func:`malloc` och :c:func:`free`.  I C++ anvûÊnds "
"operatûÑrerna ``new`` och ``delete`` med i stort sett samma innebûÑrd och vi "
"kommer att begrûÊnsa fûÑljande diskussion till C-fallet."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:882
msgid ""
"Every block of memory allocated with :c:func:`malloc` should eventually be "
"returned to the pool of available memory by exactly one call "
"to :c:func:`free`. It is important to call :c:func:`free` at the right "
"time.  If a block's address is forgotten but :c:func:`free` is not called "
"for it, the memory it occupies cannot be reused until the program "
"terminates.  This is called a :dfn:`memory leak`.  On the other hand, if a "
"program calls :c:func:`free` for a block and then continues to use the "
"block, it creates a conflict with reuse of the block through "
"another :c:func:`malloc` call.  This is called :dfn:`using freed memory`. It "
"has the same bad consequences as referencing uninitialized data --- core "
"dumps, wrong results, mysterious crashes."
msgstr ""
"Varje minnesblock som allokerats med :c:func:`malloc` bûÑr sûË smûËningom "
"ûËterfûÑras till poolen av tillgûÊngligt minne genom exakt ett anrop "
"till :c:func:`free`. Det ûÊr viktigt att anropa :c:func:`free` vid rûÊtt "
"tidpunkt.  Om adressen till ett block glûÑms bort men :c:func:`free` inte "
"anropas fûÑr det, kan det minne som det upptar inte ûËteranvûÊndas fûÑrrûÊn "
"programmet avslutas.  Detta kallas fûÑr en :dfn:`minneslûÊcka`.  û andra "
"sidan, om ett program anropar :c:func:`free` fûÑr ett block och sedan "
"fortsûÊtter att anvûÊnda blocket, skapar det en konflikt med ûËteranvûÊndning av "
"blocket genom ett annat :c:func:`malloc`-anrop.  Detta kallas :dfn:`using "
"freed memory`. Det har samma dûËliga konsekvenser som att referera till "
"oinitialiserade data --- kûÊrndumpar, felaktiga resultat, mystiska krascher."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:893
msgid ""
"Common causes of memory leaks are unusual paths through the code.  For "
"instance, a function may allocate a block of memory, do some calculation, "
"and then free the block again.  Now a change in the requirements for the "
"function may add a test to the calculation that detects an error condition "
"and can return prematurely from the function.  It's easy to forget to free "
"the allocated memory block when taking this premature exit, especially when "
"it is added later to the code.  Such leaks, once introduced, often go "
"undetected for a long time: the error exit is taken only in a small fraction "
"of all calls, and most modern machines have plenty of virtual memory, so the "
"leak only becomes apparent in a long-running process that uses the leaking "
"function frequently.  Therefore, it's important to prevent leaks from "
"happening by having a coding convention or strategy that minimizes this kind "
"of errors."
msgstr ""
"Vanliga orsaker till minneslûÊckage ûÊr ovanliga vûÊgar genom koden.  En "
"funktion kan t.ex. allokera ett minnesblock, gûÑra en berûÊkning och sedan "
"frigûÑra blocket igen.  Nu kan en ûÊndring i kraven fûÑr funktionen lûÊgga till "
"ett test i berûÊkningen som upptûÊcker ett feltillstûËnd och kan ûËtervûÊnda i "
"fûÑrtid frûËn funktionen.  Det ûÊr lûÊtt att glûÑmma att frigûÑra det allokerade "
"minnesblocket nûÊr man gûÑr denna fûÑr tidiga exit, sûÊrskilt nûÊr det lûÊggs till "
"senare i koden.  NûÊr sûËdana lûÊckor vûÊl har uppstûËtt gûËr de ofta oupptûÊckta "
"under lûËng tid: felreturen sker bara i en liten del av alla anrop, och de "
"flesta moderna maskiner har gott om virtuellt minne, sûË lûÊckan blir bara "
"uppenbar i en lûËngvarig process som anvûÊnder den lûÊckande funktionen ofta.  "
"DûÊrfûÑr ûÊr det viktigt att fûÑrhindra att lûÊckor uppstûËr genom att ha en "
"kodningskonvention eller strategi som minimerar den hûÊr typen av fel."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:906
msgid ""
"Since Python makes heavy use of :c:func:`malloc` and :c:func:`free`, it "
"needs a strategy to avoid memory leaks as well as the use of freed memory.  "
"The chosen method is called :dfn:`reference counting`.  The principle is "
"simple: every object contains a counter, which is incremented when a "
"reference to the object is stored somewhere, and which is decremented when a "
"reference to it is deleted. When the counter reaches zero, the last "
"reference to the object has been deleted and the object is freed."
msgstr ""
"Eftersom Python anvûÊnder sig mycket av :c:func:`malloc` och :c:func:`free`, "
"behûÑver det en strategi fûÑr att undvika minneslûÊckor och anvûÊndning av "
"frigjort minne.  Den valda metoden kallas :dfn:`referensrûÊkning`.  Principen "
"ûÊr enkel: varje objekt innehûËller en rûÊknare, som ûÑkas nûÊr en referens till "
"objektet lagras nûËgonstans, och som minskas nûÊr en referens till det tas "
"bort. NûÊr rûÊknaren nûËr noll har den sista referensen till objektet raderats "
"och objektet ûÊr frigjort."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:914
msgid ""
"An alternative strategy is called :dfn:`automatic garbage collection`. "
"(Sometimes, reference counting is also referred to as a garbage collection "
"strategy, hence my use of \"automatic\" to distinguish the two.)  The big "
"advantage of automatic garbage collection is that the user doesn't need to "
"call :c:func:`free` explicitly.  (Another claimed advantage is an "
"improvement in speed or memory usage --- this is no hard fact however.)  The "
"disadvantage is that for C, there is no truly portable automatic garbage "
"collector, while reference counting can be implemented portably (as long as "
"the functions :c:func:`malloc` and :c:func:`free` are available --- which "
"the C Standard guarantees). Maybe some day a sufficiently portable automatic "
"garbage collector will be available for C. Until then, we'll have to live "
"with reference counts."
msgstr ""
"En alternativ strategi kallas :dfn:`automatic garbage collection`. (Ibland "
"kallas referensrûÊkning ocksûË fûÑr en skrûÊpinsamlingsstrategi, dûÊrav min "
"anvûÊndning av \"automatisk\" fûÑr att skilja de tvûË ûËt)  Den stora fûÑrdelen "
"med automatisk garbage collection ûÊr att anvûÊndaren inte behûÑver "
"anropa :c:func:`free` explicit.  (En annan pûËstûËdd fûÑrdel ûÊr en fûÑrbûÊttring "
"av hastighet eller minnesanvûÊndning --- detta ûÊr dock inget hûËrt faktum.)  "
"Nackdelen ûÊr att det fûÑr C inte finns nûËgon verkligt portabel automatisk "
"garbage collector, medan referensrûÊkning kan implementeras portabelt (sûË "
"lûÊnge funktionerna :c:func:`malloc` och :c:func:`free` ûÊr tillgûÊngliga --- "
"vilket C-standarden garanterar). Kanske kommer en dag en tillrûÊckligt "
"portabel automatisk skrûÊpsamlare att finnas tillgûÊnglig fûÑr C. Till dess fûËr "
"vi leva med referensrûÊkning."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:926
msgid ""
"While Python uses the traditional reference counting implementation, it also "
"offers a cycle detector that works to detect reference cycles.  This allows "
"applications to not worry about creating direct or indirect circular "
"references; these are the weakness of garbage collection implemented using "
"only reference counting.  Reference cycles consist of objects which contain "
"(possibly indirect) references to themselves, so that each object in the "
"cycle has a reference count which is non-zero.  Typical reference counting "
"implementations are not able to reclaim the memory belonging to any objects "
"in a reference cycle, or referenced from the objects in the cycle, even "
"though there are no further references to the cycle itself."
msgstr ""
"Python anvûÊnder den traditionella referensrûÊkningsimplementeringen, men "
"erbjuder ocksûË en cykeldetektor som upptûÊcker referenscykler.  Detta gûÑr att "
"applikationer inte behûÑver oroa sig fûÑr att skapa direkta eller indirekta "
"cirkulûÊra referenser; dessa ûÊr svagheten hos skrûÊpsamling som implementeras "
"med endast referensrûÊkning.  Referenscykler bestûËr av objekt som innehûËller "
"(eventuellt indirekta) referenser till sig sjûÊlva, sûË att varje objekt i "
"cykeln har ett referensantal som inte ûÊr noll.  Typiska implementationer av "
"referensrûÊkning kan inte ûËterta det minne som tillhûÑr nûËgot objekt i en "
"referenscykel, eller som refereras frûËn objekten i cykeln, ûÊven om det inte "
"finns nûËgra ytterligare referenser till sjûÊlva cykeln."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:937
msgid ""
"The cycle detector is able to detect garbage cycles and can reclaim them. "
"The :mod:`gc` module exposes a way to run the detector "
"(the :func:`~gc.collect` function), as well as configuration interfaces and "
"the ability to disable the detector at runtime."
msgstr ""
"Cykeldetektorn kan upptûÊcka skrûÊpcykler och kan ûËterta dem. "
"Modulen :mod:`gc` exponerar ett sûÊtt att kûÑra detektorn "
"(funktionen :func:`~gc.collect`), samt konfigurationsgrûÊnssnitt och "
"mûÑjligheten att inaktivera detektorn vid kûÑrning."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:946
msgid "Reference Counting in Python"
msgstr "ReferensrûÊkning i Python"

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:948
msgid ""
"There are two macros, ``Py_INCREF(x)`` and ``Py_DECREF(x)``, which handle "
"the incrementing and decrementing of the reference "
"count. :c:func:`Py_DECREF` also frees the object when the count reaches "
"zero. For flexibility, it doesn't call :c:func:`free` directly --- rather, "
"it makes a call through a function pointer in the object's :dfn:`type "
"object`.  For this purpose (and others), every object also contains a "
"pointer to its type object."
msgstr ""
"Det finns tvûË makron, ``Py_INCREF(x)`` och ``Py_DECREF(x)``, som hanterar "
"inkrementering och dekrementering av referensantalet. :c:func:`Py_DECREF` "
"frigûÑr ocksûË objektet nûÊr antalet nûËr noll. FûÑr flexibilitetens skull "
"anropar den inte :c:func:`free` direkt --- utan den gûÑr ett anrop via en "
"funktionspekare i objektets :dfn:`type object`.  FûÑr detta ûÊndamûËl (och "
"andra) innehûËller varje objekt ocksûË en pekare till sitt typobjekt."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:955
msgid ""
"The big question now remains: when to use ``Py_INCREF(x)`` and "
"``Py_DECREF(x)``? Let's first introduce some terms.  Nobody \"owns\" an "
"object; however, you can :dfn:`own a reference` to an object.  An object's "
"reference count is now defined as the number of owned references to it.  The "
"owner of a reference is responsible for calling :c:func:`Py_DECREF` when the "
"reference is no longer needed.  Ownership of a reference can be "
"transferred.  There are three ways to dispose of an owned reference: pass it "
"on, store it, or call :c:func:`Py_DECREF`. Forgetting to dispose of an owned "
"reference creates a memory leak."
msgstr ""
"Nu ûËterstûËr den stora frûËgan: nûÊr ska man anvûÊnda ``Py_INCREF(x)`` och "
"``Py_DECREF(x)``? LûËt oss fûÑrst introducera nûËgra termer.  Ingen \"ûÊger\" "
"ett objekt, men du kan :dfn:`ûÊga en referens` till ett objekt.  Ett objekts "
"referensantal definieras nu som antalet ûÊgda referenser till det.  ûgaren "
"till en referens ûÊr ansvarig fûÑr att anropa :c:func:`Py_DECREF` nûÊr "
"referensen inte lûÊngre behûÑvs.  ûganderûÊtten till en referens kan "
"ûÑverfûÑras.  Det finns tre sûÊtt att gûÑra sig av med en ûÊgd referens: skicka "
"den vidare, lagra den eller anropa :c:func:`Py_DECREF`. Om man glûÑmmer att "
"gûÑra sig av med en ûÊgd referens uppstûËr en minneslûÊcka."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:964
msgid ""
"It is also possible to :dfn:`borrow` [#]_ a reference to an object.  The "
"borrower of a reference should not call :c:func:`Py_DECREF`.  The borrower "
"must not hold on to the object longer than the owner from which it was "
"borrowed. Using a borrowed reference after the owner has disposed of it "
"risks using freed memory and should be avoided completely [#]_."
msgstr ""
"Det ûÊr ocksûË mûÑjligt att :dfn:`lûËna` [#]_ en referens till ett objekt.  "
"LûËntagaren av en referens bûÑr inte anropa :c:func:`Py_DECREF`.  LûËntagaren "
"fûËr inte behûËlla objektet lûÊngre ûÊn ûÊgaren frûËn vilken det lûËnades. Att "
"anvûÊnda en lûËnad referens efter att ûÊgaren har gjort sig av med den riskerar "
"att anvûÊnda frigjort minne och bûÑr undvikas helt [#]_."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:970
msgid ""
"The advantage of borrowing over owning a reference is that you don't need to "
"take care of disposing of the reference on all possible paths through the "
"code --- in other words, with a borrowed reference you don't run the risk of "
"leaking when a premature exit is taken.  The disadvantage of borrowing over "
"owning is that there are some subtle situations where in seemingly correct "
"code a borrowed reference can be used after the owner from which it was "
"borrowed has in fact disposed of it."
msgstr ""
"FûÑrdelen med att lûËna en referens jûÊmfûÑrt med att ûÊga den ûÊr att du inte "
"behûÑver ta hand om referensen pûË alla mûÑjliga vûÊgar genom koden --- med "
"andra ord, med en lûËnad referens lûÑper du inte risken att lûÊcka nûÊr en fûÑr "
"tidig exit tas.  Nackdelen med att lûËna i stûÊllet fûÑr att ûÊga ûÊr att det "
"finns vissa subtila situationer dûÊr en lûËnad referens i till synes korrekt "
"kod kan anvûÊndas efter att ûÊgaren som den lûËnades frûËn i sjûÊlva verket har "
"gjort sig av med den."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:978
msgid ""
"A borrowed reference can be changed into an owned reference by "
"calling :c:func:`Py_INCREF`.  This does not affect the status of the owner "
"from which the reference was borrowed --- it creates a new owned reference, "
"and gives full owner responsibilities (the new owner must dispose of the "
"reference properly, as well as the previous owner)."
msgstr ""
"En lûËnad referens kan ûÊndras till en ûÊgd referens genom att "
"anropa :c:func:`Py_INCREF`.  Detta pûËverkar inte statusen fûÑr den ûÊgare frûËn "
"vilken referensen lûËnades --- det skapar en ny ûÊgd referens och ger ûÊgaren "
"fullt ansvar (den nya ûÊgaren mûËste gûÑra sig av med referensen pûË rûÊtt sûÊtt, "
"liksom den tidigare ûÊgaren)."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:988
msgid "Ownership Rules"
msgstr "Regler fûÑr ûÊgande"

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:990
msgid ""
"Whenever an object reference is passed into or out of a function, it is part "
"of the function's interface specification whether ownership is transferred "
"with the reference or not."
msgstr ""
"NûÊr en objektreferens skickas in i eller ut ur en funktion ûÊr det en del av "
"funktionens grûÊnssnittsspecifikation om ûÊganderûÊtten ûÑverfûÑrs med referensen "
"eller inte."

#: ../../extending/extending.rst:994
msgid ""
"Most functions that return a reference to an object pass on ownership with "
"the reference.  In particular, all functions whose function it is to create "
"a new object, such as :c:func:`PyLong_FromLong` and :c:func:`Py_BuildValue`, "
